<h1>Introduction</h1>

<p>R Markdown lets you combine text, math notation, and R code in one document. You write your explanation in plain text and insert executable code chunks that run during knitting.</p>

<p>Inline math looks like this: <span>α + β = γ</span></p>

<p>Displayed equation:</p>

<p>
$$
y = \alpha + \beta x
$$
</p>

